  "body": " Relative Rate of Change   Relative Change and Percentage Change   The relative change of a quantity , is the ratio, The percentage change of is the relative change of , expressed as a percentage, or,      Sensitivity to Change   If a small change in produces a large change in , then we say that the function is sensitive to changes in .   In this way, the derivative is a measure of the sensitivity of the to changes in .    Relative Growth Rate and the Natural Logarithm  In economics and other fields, the relative growth of something is much more important than its absolute growth.   Let represent a quantity over time. Then, the relative rate of change of is given by,    This gives RRC as a decimal, which can be written as a percentage by multiplying by 100. Notice that,   That is, the relative growth rate is the rate of change of the natural logarithm of the original outputs . This is another reason why logarithms with base are considered natural.   "
