  "title": "Rectilinear Motion Revisited",
  "body": " Rectilinear Motion Revisited  Recall that if represents the position of an object along a straight line, then its velocity is given by , and its acceleration is given by .   If , then the particle is moving to the right . If , then the particle is moving to the left.  The particle is at rest if .  The particle changes direction if changes sign (either from positive to negative, or vise versa).  If , then the particle is accelerating to the right. If , then the particle is accelerating to the left.  If and have the same sign, then the particle is speeding up . If and have opposite signs, then the particle is slowing down .   "
